1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy describes how VOLKA ENTERTAINMENT LIMITED (“VOLKA”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) collects and uses your personal data, and your rights and choices concerning your personal data.
This Privacy Policy applies when you use our Service which comprises VOLKA’s game (the “Game”), website, and related services. By accepting this Policy, you agree to our collection, storage, use, disclosure, transfer (including cross-border transfer) of your personal data as stated in the Policy. If you are at all concerned about the way we use your personal data, please refrain from using our Service.
We may change this Privacy Policy from time to time, in which case we will notify you. If you do not agree to the then-current version of our Privacy Policy, you must stop using our Service.
If you are a California, Virginia, Colorado, Connecticut, Utah, Oregon or Texas resident, please review our
United States Privacy Notice
.
The data controller: VOLKA ENTERTAINMENT LIMITED
Address: 3, Kleopatras Street, 3042 Limassol, Cyprus
Email:
info@volkagames.com
Data Protection Officer
Address: 3, Kleopatras Street, 3042 Limassol, Cyprus
Email:
privacy@volka.com
2. Definitions
For the purposes of this Policy:
“personal data” means any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person
“processing” means any operation or set of operations which is performed on personal data or on sets of personal data, whether or not by automated means, such as collection, recording, organisation, structuring, storage, adaptation or alteration, retrieval, consultation, use, disclosure by transmission, dissemination or otherwise making available, alignment or combination, restriction, erasure or destruction
“controller” means the natural or legal person, public authority, agency, or other body which determines the purposes and means of the processing of personal data
“processor” means a natural or legal person, public authority, agency, or other body which processes personal data on behalf of the controller
3. Data We Collect and How
We collect personal data that you provide to us directly when creating an account or communicating with us. When you use our Service, including any chat feature, we will collect information about the ways in which you use and interact with our Service. We may also collect or receive information about you from third parties connected to our Service.
Data you give us
Contact information: name, email address.
Player profile and account information: name, username, password, email address, profile photo, language.
Communications to the Service: messages sent to the support team and other correspondence with us, your public posts or comments in our official page, game reviews and feedback you submit about our Service, messages or information sent through any chat features within the Service to other users.
Data we collect automatically
Game-related data: Game ID (created by VOLKA and used to identify your account), gameplay data, including game progress, levels, session length, in-game purchases, game preferences, interactions with other players, other in-game activities.
Technical data: IP address, device type, operating system, platform, device settings, device identifiers, browser type and version, language, browser plugin versions.
Usage data: date and time of activity on our Service, features used, content viewed or engaged with, pages viewed and the order of those pages, amount of time spent on a page, page interaction information (such as scrolling, clicks, and mouse-overs), referring/exit pages and URLs.
The collection of this information involves the use of cookies and similar technologies. For more information about how we use cookies and similar technologies and how you can manage or disable them, please read our
Cookies Policy
.
Data we obtain from third-party sources
Data from third-party platforms if you choose to link them to our Service (Facebook, Google, app stores). For example, if you access the Game from your Facebook account, we may receive any information from your Facebook profile that you or Facebook shares with us. Such information may include your Facebook user identification number (Facebook ID number) and information about your use of the Game. If you access the Game from your Google account, we may receive your Google email address and avatar. The information we receive depends on your privacy settings on these third-party platforms. We advise you to carefully read their terms of service and privacy policy so that you understand how they use your personal data and what might be shared, and if necessary, to modify your privacy settings directly on their service.
Data from advertising and analytics providers we work with. These third parties may set and read their own cookies and similar technologies to collect information through our Service and provide us with demographic data, analytics, and other aggregated data. These data do not directly or indirectly identify any individual.
4. How We Use Your Data
We use your personal data for various purposes. You can access some parts of our Service without giving us your personal data. However, to create an account and play our Game, you will need to provide your personal data.
We will use your personal data under several legal bases including to perform our contract with you (i.e., our
Terms of Service
), to comply with a legal obligation, to pursue our legitimate interests (provided that these are not overridden by your interests or rights), or with your consent.
We have listed the purposes for which we will use your personal data and the legal bases we rely upon to do so in the table below.
PURPOSE
LEGAL BASIS
To create your game account and allow you to play our Game and use our Service.
Performance of contract
To enable in-game purchases.
Performance of contract
To respond to your questions, comments, requests, and complaints as well as to provide player support.
