(b) Legitimate interests – protecting and running our business; keeping our Service and its chat features safe and fair; managing security, network and information security; risk and fraud prevention; protecting the safety and well-being of players
5. Data Sharing
We may share your personal data with the following categories of third parties:
Business partners and third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as mobile platforms and social networks, software providers, providers of technical support, player support, email and notification services, payment service providers, data analytics, marketing, advertising, data storage, website security services. These partners handle the data in compliance with data protection laws and only as instructed by VOLKA.
With some of these partners, we only share anonymous information, i.e., information which does not directly or indirectly disclose your identity. For example, we may share anonymous and aggregated information with our advertising partners (such as Compado and WeLoveX). Such information may include technical data, unique identifiers, game statistics and behaviour, advertisement performance data. We may also allow our advertisers to collect anonymous and aggregated information within the Service and they may then share that information with us. Our advertisers may collect this information through the use of cookies and other similar tracking technologies. This enables our advertisers to deliver targeted advertising in order to personalise your experience by showing you advertisements for products and services that are more likely to be of interest to you. Advertisers will also use this information to measure advertising effectiveness and improve their operations. You can opt out of targeted advertising by following the instructions in section 9 below. We may also share anonymous data with our consent management platforms, including OneTrust and Usercentrics. This data typically consists of records of user interactions with our Service. By using these platforms, we aim to enhance your privacy and ensure compliance with relevant data protection laws.
Public authorities and other organisations. We will disclose your personal data if we are required to do so in order to comply with any laws or regulations, to respond to lawful requests by public authorities, including for national security, law enforcement, or legal process purposes, to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violation of our
Terms of Service
.
Other users of our Service. The Service may include chat features where you can post messages and communicate with other users. When posting information to any chat feature, please be aware that such information is made available to other users. Therefore, please avoid disclosing any of your personal data to other users through any chat feature.
We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties.
6. International Data Transfers
We may transfer the personal data we collect to countries other than the country in which the data originally was collected. We store your personal data on servers located in the European Economic Area (“EEA”) and in the United States, and we may also process these data in other countries (including outside the EEA) where our business partners and service providers operate. We take steps to ensure that your data are transferred to third countries which have been recognised as providing an adequate level of protection, otherwise, that appropriate safeguards are in place, such as by the use of standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission for transfers of data from inside the EEA to a country outside the EEA. If you would like to learn more about these safeguards, please write to our Data Protection Officer at
privacy@volka.com
. If you are not satisfied with the safeguards we implement and you do not want your personal data to be transferred in third countries, unfortunately, you should request us to erase your personal data and you should stop using our Service.
For more details about where we transfer your personal data, please see the information below.
