7. Data Retention
We will retain your personal data for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. We will delete your data if you request us to erase your personal data (see section 9 below).
Please note that, even after you have asked us to erase your data, we may retain some of your personal data where necessary to enable us to meet our legal obligations, to exercise or defend legal claims, or for other purposes as permissible by law. We also reserve the right to depersonalise your data (remove all direct or indirect references to your identity) and continue using it for our own legitimate interests, such as for research and statistical purposes.
Your personal data will be destroyed without delay once they become unnecessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. Your personal data is stored in electronic format. We destroy your personal data within our systems through technical means which make the personal data permanently unrecoverable.
Information you have disclosed to other users through the Service, including without limitation through any chat feature, may remain visible to other users after you have asked us to erase your data. Such information will show an anonymised account as its source. We do not control the information that other users copy out of our Service. Therefore, please avoid disclosing any of your personal data to other users through our Service.
8. Data Security
We have implemented reasonable and appropriate security measures to protect your personal data against loss, destruction, alteration, misuse, unauthorised access or disclosure. In addition, we take reasonable steps to ensure that third parties to whom we disclose or transfer any data will provide sufficient protection of your data.
Please be aware that, in spite of all precautions we take, no security system can prevent all potential security breaches. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data. We urge you to take steps to keep your personal information, including your account information, secure and to be careful when you submit or transmit any data through the Service, including through any chat feature.
9. Your Rights and Options
Under the data protection laws, you have the following rights:
Right of access to your personal data, which allows you to obtain a copy of the data we hold about you and other supplementary information about our privacy practices with respect to your personal data.
Right to have inaccurate personal data rectified or incomplete personal data completed.
Right to have your personal data erased in certain circumstances; for example, where there is no good reason for us to continue processing them, where you have withdrawn your consent, or you have objected to the processing of your personal data (see below). The erasure of your personal data leads to the permanent loss of access to your game account.
Right to request restriction of processing of your personal data in certain circumstances; for example, while we are considering a rectification or objection request made by you.
Right to data portability, which allows you to receive the personal data that you have provided to us, in a structured, commonly used and machine readable format, and also to request that your personal data be transmitted to another controller.
Right to object to the processing of your personal data, on grounds relating to your particular situation and in certain circumstances such as where we are relying on our legitimate business interests as the legal ground for processing, or where personal data are processed for direct marketing purposes.
Right to withdraw your consent at any time if we are processing your personal data with your consent.
Right to lodge a complaint about the way we handle your personal data with your local data protection authority.
To exercise any of your rights specified above, please submit a request via our Support directly within the Game.
We will try to respond to any such request as soon as possible, but we will always do so within the time limit set by the applicable data protection law.
Opt out of direct marketing. Where permitted by applicable laws, VOLKA may send you marketing emails. If you want to stop receiving promotional emails from VOLKA, click on the “unsubscribe” link at the bottom of any promotional email from VOLKA. Please be aware that you may still receive non-promotional emails from us, including those related to the Service, updates to our
Terms of Service
or Privacy Policy, and transactional information (for example, details about your purchases on the Service). If you want to stop receiving push notifications, which are messages an app or website sends you on your mobile device or web browser even when the app or site is not active, you can turn off push notifications by going to your mobile device or browser settings.
Opt out of targeted advertising. You can opt out of interest-based advertising by adjusting your device or your browser settings:
For iOS devices: go to Settings > Privacy > Apple Advertising and turn off “Personalized Ads”.
For Android devices: go to Settings > Google services > Ads and enable “Opt out of Ads Personalisation”.
You can also reset the “Advertising Identifier” from your mobile device settings page, which will prevent continued use of existing behavioral data tied to your previous “Advertising Identifier”.
For display advertising on the Web, you can also adjust your browser settings to limit certain tracking by means of cookies, and by visiting the following sites:
http://www.aboutads.info/choices
and
http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/
.
To opt out of targeted ads on Facebook, please visit this
page
.
Please note that, even if you use your right to opt out, you will still receive advertising, but the advertising you see may be less relevant to your interests.
10. Automated Decision-Making
In some instances, our use of your personal data may result in automated decision-making, including profiling. Automated decision-making is the process of making a decision concerning you by automated means (using software algorithms) without any human involvement. For example, we use automated decisions to provide direct or targeted advertising on our Service. You can exercise your right to object to such processing or opt out of direct or targeted advertising as described in section 9 above.
We do not carry out any decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal effects or similarly significantly affects any user.
11. Children
Our Service is available only to individuals who are at least 16 years old. If you are under the age of 16, you must obtain permission from your parent or legal guardian before using our Service and submitting your personal data.
We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 16, or process such information without parental consent. If we learn that we have inadvertently done so, we will try to take steps to promptly delete such data from our records. If you believe that we might have collected personal data from a child under the age of 16 without parental consent, please contact us.
12. Links to Third Parties
Our Service may contain links to third-party websites. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to that third-party’s site and will be subject to their own privacy policy. We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies or practices of any third-party sites or services. You should always review the privacy policy of each site you visit.
13. Governing Language
This Privacy Policy has been drafted in the English language, which is the original and controlling version of this Privacy Policy. All translations of this Privacy Policy into other languages shall be solely for convenience and shall not control the meaning or application of this Privacy Policy. In case of any inconsistency or discrepancy between a translated version of this Privacy Policy and the English version, the English version shall prevail.
14. Contact Us
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy or our data protection practices, please contact our Data Protection Officer at
privacy@volka.com
. For general enquiries, you may contact our Support team.
